## 7. Deploy
- Deploy target: backend API and web SPA are deployed together on the same host.
- Deploy trigger: automatic on push to `main` (or manual `workflow_dispatch`) via `.github/workflows/deploy.yml`.
- Path filters for auto-deploy: `backend/**`, `web/**`, `scripts/deploy.sh`, `.cpanel.yml`, `.github/workflows/deploy.yml`.
- Frontend prerequisite: run `npm run build:prod` from repository root and commit `web/dist/` before pushing.
- Artifact guardrail: `.github/workflows/web-ci.yml` verifies `web/dist/` and built assets exist.
- Deployment flow:
  1. GitHub Actions calls cPanel UAPI `VersionControl/update` for `/home/crointhe/repositories/tastespot`.
  2. GitHub Actions calls cPanel UAPI `VersionControlDeployment/create`.
  3. cPanel executes `.cpanel.yml`, which runs `bash /home/crointhe/repositories/tastespot/scripts/deploy.sh`.
  4. `scripts/deploy.sh` performs: repo clean + pull, backend copy (excluding `storage`), Laravel migrate/cache/link, permissions setup, SPA publish (`web/dist/*` to `public/`) with `index.html` existence check.
- Required GitHub secrets: `CPANEL_USER`, `CPANEL_TOKEN`.
- Verification after deploy:
  - Last run in GitHub Actions is green.
  - `GET /api/v1/ping` returns healthy status.
  - `https://tastespot.crointhemorning.com/` serves SPA HTML.
- Source of truth files: `.github/workflows/deploy.yml`, `.github/workflows/web-ci.yml`, `.cpanel.yml`, `scripts/deploy.sh`, `backend/DEPLOY.md`.